description: From eventual +‎ -ly. The third sense is influenced by any of several European languages, including Czech eventuálně, Swedish eventuellt.

entries.meaning: In the end; at some later time, especially after a long time, a series of problems, struggles, delays or setbacks.
examples: Everyone's true colors will be revealed eventually.

entries.meaning: (mathematics, of a sequence) For some tail; for all terms beyond some term; with only finitely many exceptions.
examples: Eventually, all prime numbers are odd.

entries.meaning: (proscribed, non-native speakers' English) Possibly, potentially, perhaps
examples: I will come eventually, but haven't decided yet.
